ory:Chinese rhythmic gymnasts]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Taiyuan]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Gymnasts from Shanxi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athlete|name=Zhang Doudou|native_name={{linktext|\u5f20|\u8c46|\u8c46}}|nationality=China|birth_date={{birth date and age|1996|07|23}}|retired=2017|birth_place=[[Taiyuan]], [[Shanxi]], China|occupation=Rhythmic gymnast|years_active=2006-2017|sport=[[Rhythmic gymnastics]]}}'''Zhang Doudou''' ({{Lang-zh|c=\u5f20\u8c46\u8c46|s=|t=|p=Zh\u0101ng D\u00f2ud\u00f2u}}; born July 23, 1996) is a retired Chinese [[Rhythmic gymnastics|rhythmic gymnast]] from [[Taiyuan]], [[Shanxi]], China. In 2013, she won the 6th on the [[World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]].<ref name=\":7\" /> In January 2014, she was assessed as \"International Sports Master\" by [[State General Administration of Sports]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sport.gov.cn/n16/n33193/n33208/n33433/n33688/4946481.html|title=\u7ade\u4f53\u53f8\u5173\u4e8e\u5bf9\u6388\u4e88\u56fd\u9645\u7ea7\u8fd0\u52a8\u5065\u5c06\u548c\u8fd0\u52a8\u5065\u5c06\u79f0\u53f7\u8fd0\u52a8\u5458\u516c\u793a\u7684\u901a\u77e5|date=3 January 2014|website=\u56fd\u5bb6\u4f53\u80b2\u603b\u5c40|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nShe retired in August 2017.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://sports.ifeng.com/a/20170823/51724685_0.shtml#p=1|title=\u4f53\u575b\u5973\u795e\u9eef\u7136\u9000\u5f79 \u56e0\u633a\u80f8\u7167\u4e00\u591c\u8d70\u7ea2|date=23 August 2017|website=\u51e4\u51f0\u7f51|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn August 2006, Zhang Doudou competed in the National Champtionships of Rhythmic Gymnastics for Teenagers as a member of Shanxi's team in [[Zhuhai]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://news.sohu.com/20060830/n245064367.shtml|title=\u5c71\u897f\u535a\u7ef4\u827a\u4f53\u593a\u5168\u56fd\u827a\u672f\u4f53\u64cd\u8d5b\u4f73\u7ee9|date=30 August 2006|website=\u641c\u72d0\u7f51|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2009, she competed in the 11th [[National Games of China]] in [[Dezhou]]. In hoop gymnastics, she ranked fourth,<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://sports.sohu.com/20091018/n267470696.shtml|title=\u56fe\u6587\uff1a\u827a\u672f\u4f53\u64cd\u56e2\u4f53\u603b\u5206\u8d5b\u51b5 \u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u5708\u64cd\u6bd4\u8d5b\u4e2d|date=18 October 2009|website=\u641c\u72d0\u4f53\u80b2|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref> and in ball gymnastics, she ranked fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/o/p/2009-10-18/17034642178.shtml|title=\u56fe\u6587-\u5168\u8fd0\u827a\u672f\u4f53\u64cd\u56e2\u4f53\u603b\u5206\u8d5b\u51b5 \u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u6bd4\u8d5b\u7403\u64cd|date=18 October 2009|website=\u65b0\u6d6a\u4f53\u80b2|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, Zhang Doudou competed in the 12th [[National Games of China]] in [[Shenyang]], and ranked 6th of Group All-Around as a member of Shanxi's team. After that, she won an award named \"Sportsman of the Year\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/166884716_546108|title=\u4f53\u575b\u5973\u795e\u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u7d20\u989c\u79d2\u6740\u4f17\u5973\u661f \u9000\u5f79\u8fdb\u519b\u5a31\u4e50\u5708\uff1f|date=24 August 2017|website=\u641c\u72d0\u5a31\u4e50|language=zh|access-date=5 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, Zhang Doudou competed in the 2015 National Champtionships of Rhythmic Gymnastics in [[Xi'an]].<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://gymnastics.sport.org.cn/cga/inland_rhythmic/2015-04-23/469077.html|title=2015\u5168\u56fd\u827a\u4f53\u4e2a\u4eba\u51a0\u519b\u8d5b\u95ed\u5e55 \u672a\u6765\u9886\u519b\u8005\u6d6e\u51fa\u6c34\u9762|date=23 April 2015|website=\u4e2d\u534e\u5168\u56fd\u4f53\u80b2\u603b\u4f1a\u5b98\u65b9\u7f51\u7ad9|publisher=\u4e2d\u56fd\u4f53\u64cd\u534f\u4f1a|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref> In September, she competed in [[World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]] in [[Stuttgart]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.china.com.cn/v/sports/2015-09/10/content_36547044.htm|title=2015\u827a\u672f\u4f53\u64cd\u4e16\u9526\u8d5b \"\u5973\u795e\"\u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u9886\u8854\u51fa\u6218|date=10 September 2015|website=\u89c6\u9891\u4e2d\u56fd|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.163.com/15/0911/00/B36L6RQ400014AED.html|title=\u201c\u827a\u4f53\u5973\u795e\u201d\u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u4eae\u76f8\u4e16\u9526\u8d5b|date=11 September 2015|website=\u7f51\u6613|publisher=\u6d59\u6c5f\u5728\u7ebf-\u7ecd\u5174\u53bf\u62a5|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2017, she competed in the 13th [[National Games of China]] with [[Zhao Yating]] as members of Shanxi's team, and Zhang Doudou ranked 8th.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sx.xinhuanet.com/2017-08/21/c_1121514725.htm|title=\u5168\u8fd0\u4f1a\u827a\u672f\u4f53\u64cd\u4e2a\u4eba\u5168\u80fd\u8d5b\u4fe9\u201c\u5973\u795e\u201d\u6539\u5199\u5c71\u897f\u7eaa\u5f55|date=21 August 2017|website=\u65b0\u534e\u7f51|language=zh|access-date=6 April 2018}}</ref> She retired after the competition.<ref name=\":1\" /> After retirement, she became a coach of the National Rhythmic Gymnast Team.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite news|url=http://tyrb.tynews.com.cn/jrgz/c/2019-03/29/content_1724581.htm|title=\u6e05\u5f90\u5973\u5b69\u5f20\u8c46\u8c46\u7684\u91c7\u706b\u8bb0|last=|first=|date=29 March 2019|work=\u592a\u539f\u65e5\u62a5|access-date=7 April 2019|language=zh}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Zhang obtained the Olimpic Flame of the Second National Youth Games.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n== Personal statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Competition\n!Event\n!Result\n!References\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2006\n| rowspan=\"3\" |National Champtionships of Rhythmic Gymnastics \nfor Teenagers\n|Group All-Around\n|3rd\n| rowspan=\"3\" |<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|All-Around\n|4th\n|-\n|Ribbon\n|3rd\n|-\n|2009\n|The 11th [[National Games of China]]\n|All-Around\n|20.500, 4th\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n